 in a virtually bloodless coup. His comeback was seen as a welcome return to strongman rule. Leftist military officers assisted in the overthrow. Daoud Khan abolished the 1964 constitution and established the Republic of Afghanistan, with himself as chair
man of the Central Committee of the Republic and prime minister. King Zahir Shah went into exile in Rome.
