Eastern Kati are Lutdek, Badamuk, Bargromatal, Aptzai, Ptzigrom, and Ahmad-I Devana. Between the two Kati groups lies the Peich River Valley, which is occupied by the Prazun.  Their important villages are Pashkigrom, Tussumgrom, Lewergrom, Prunsgrom, and 
